epsilon(x) returns the smallest positive number e such that 1 + e > 1.

default real examples:
epsilon(1.0) = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(x)   = 1.192093e-07

epsilon depends on kind, not value:
epsilon(0.0)       = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(1.0)       = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(10.0)      = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(huge(0.0)) = 1.192093e-07

array element examples:
a =  0 1 10 3.402823e+38
epsilon(a(1)) = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(a(2)) = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(a(3)) = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(a(4)) = 1.192093e-07

real kind examples:
epsilon(1.0_4) = 1.192093e-07
epsilon(1.0_8) = 2.22044604925031e-16
